Parking Hunter — Product Characterization
The Problem
Finding parking in a city is frustrating. Drivers waste time circling blocks looking for a free spot, with no real-time information about where spaces are available.

The Solution
Parking Hunter is a crowd-sourced, gamified parking finder — like Waze, but for parking spots. Users report free spots in real time, and the community keeps the data fresh. The more people use it, the better it gets.

Target Audience
Urban drivers in busy cities
Daily commuters
Anyone who parks on the street regularly
How It Works
You find a free spot → open the app, tap the hunter button
Take a photo → AI scans it and confirms the spot is actually free
Pin your location → spot appears on the map for everyone nearby
Spot expires in 30 minutes → unless someone confirms it's still free
Someone takes the spot → they mark it as taken, it disappears instantly
Key Features
Map
Full-screen dark map showing free spots nearby in real time
Color-coded markers: green (high confidence), yellow (medium), red (low)
Spot details: photo, time reported, AI confidence score, countdown to expiry
AI Verification
Every reported spot is scanned by Claude Vision AI
AI returns: is it free? confidence % and reason
Prevents fake or incorrect reports
Gamification
Earn points for every spot you report (+10 pts)
Bonus points when your spot gets confirmed by others (+5 pts)
Level up from Level 1 to Level 5
Unlock badges: First Hunt, Speed Demon, Gold Hunter, Night Owl, and more
Global leaderboard — compete with other hunters in your city
Authentication
Sign in with Google, Apple, or Email
Demo mode — try the full app without signing in
